{"article_id":"7X4DsQSFGY8U8X3M","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Bernie Sanders won the New Hampshire primary Tuesday night .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Second-place finisher Pete Buttigieg earned 24.4 percent of the vote ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"while Amy Klobuchar ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"not long ago polling in single digits ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"came out of nowhere with 19.8 percent , a classic New Hampshire outlier result .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"The words \" eked \" and \" narrowly \" are getting a workout in headlines today .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"There is a Yeah , but... passage in nearly every major media write-up of Bernie ' s win .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"\" Sanders cements his front-runner status ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"but his narrow margins... show how volatile this race is , \" is how The New York Times put it .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"In reality , the results for Sanders cut both ways .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"On one hand , it ' s amazing","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"he can win any state","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"after years of propaganda","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"depicting him as a half-dead cross of Hitler and Stalin","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"( MSNBC","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"before New Hampshire outdid itself with Looney Tunes commentary about \" executions in Central Park \" and a \" digital brownshirt brigade \" ) .","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"On the other hand , there are signs after New Hampshire","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"that some of the relentless corporate messaging against Sanders is landing .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"This will inspire orgies of excitement","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"- it ' s already happening -","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"as pundits revel in every storyline","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"suggesting","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"Democratic voters are scrambling to find an \" electable \" alternative .","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"Good .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Let them .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"I saw this movie in 2016","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"and have a fair idea","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"of how it ends .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"It just won ' t be horrifying this time .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Four years ago , after New Hampshire , it was crystal clear that Donald Trump was not only going to win his party ' s nomination ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"but that his path was being actively cleared by the Republican Party establishment and the national news media ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"whose half-baked efforts","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"to stop him","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"were working in reverse .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"I wrote this in February 2016 :","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"The","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"[ Republicans ]","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"sent forth","depth":16},{"id":38,"text":"to take on Trump","depth":16},{"id":39,"text":"have been so incompetent ,","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"they can ' t even lose properly .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"One GOP strategist put it this way :","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"\" Maybe 34 [ percent ] is Trump ' s ceiling .","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"But 34 in a five-person race wins... \"","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"The numbers simply don ' t work ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"unless the field unexpectedly narrows before March .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Early mixed results guaranteed","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"that Ted Cruz , John Kasich , Jeb Bush , and Marco Rubio would not drop out soon enough","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"to give any of the others a chance .","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"As a result , the following was obvious at this time four years ago :","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"\" Trump will probably enjoy at least a five-horse race through Super Tuesday . \"","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"In hindsight , those Republican challengers were so villainously terrible","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"that none would have beaten Trump in a two-person race .","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"Still , Bush ' s backers knew","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"their man was roadkill by New Hampshire ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"yet didn ' t pull the plug .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Kasich ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"who in a rare moment of self-awareness was ready to bail after Iowa","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"( \" If we get smoked up there ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"I ' m going back to Ohio ,","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"\" he fumed in New Hampshire ) ,","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"let himself be fooled by one surprise second-place finish .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"All pledged to be committed to stopping Trump","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"but accelerated his victory","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"by staying in too long .","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"Popular disgust was also enhanced by delusional news-media hype","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"surrounding a succession of would-be \" real \" candidates .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"All of this is happening all over again ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"only this time it ' s Democrats","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"who are committing ritualistic self-abuse ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"seemingly in a conspiracy with one another and the news media","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"to push as many votes as possible to a hated outsider .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"I thought","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"this outcome might be possible for Bernie nearly a year ago :","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"The 30,000-foot pundit view on Sanders ' chances should be that he , of course , has a chance , one","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"rooted in the same logic","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"that saw Trump win .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"He is an unconventional candidate with an at least somewhat insoluble base of support ,","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"running in an overlarge field of mostly traditional politicians ,","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"many of whom will take votes from one another .","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"Still , no one could have predicted","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"that even the idiosyncratic particulars of the 2016 and 2020 races would be so alike .","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"In 2016 , Iowa ' s Republican caucus was won by Cruz ,","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"but press wizards gushed over the \" Marcomentum \" of third-place Rubio ,","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"who acted","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"like he ' d won","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"with a soaringly pompous address","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"that somehow evoked both Obama and Henry V :","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"They told me","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that we have no chance","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"because my hair wasn ' t gray enough","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"and my boots were too high...","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"But tonight , tonight here in Iowa , the people of this great state have sent a very clear message .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Four days before the New Hampshire vote , Rubio stepped on a rake in a debate ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"repeating the","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"\" let ' s dispel with the fiction","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"that Barack Obama doesn ' t know what he ' s doing \"","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"schtick four times in a viral fiasco .","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"The New York Times declared \" the End of Marcomentum \"","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"roughly 10 days after it began .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"This year the standout haughty victory declaration in Iowa was given by a different human haircut , Pete Buttigieg ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"who told Iowans","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"\" you have shocked the nation , \"","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"with zero percent of the vote in .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Unlike Rubio , Pete could argue","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"he technically won ,","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"but otherwise , the story was the same .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Press swooned","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"- \" # Pete-mentum is no joke , \"","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"declared the Daily News -","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"only to watch","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"as the Great Electable Hope stepped on a rake in the New Hampshire debate ,","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"with Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar both kicking him in the balls on his race record .","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"Like clockwork , Pete was no longer the new hotness .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"With about 10 percent of the results in Tuesday night , Gloria Borger on CNN opened the floodgates on the inevitable next gambit .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"\" Klomentum ? \"","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"she asked Anderson Cooper .","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"The latter responded , correctly ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"that the horrible word sounded like something","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"he took for his sciatica .","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"Klomentum was instantly a thing .","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"\" [ Cory ] Booker and [ Kamala ] Harris","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"looking at # Klomentum tonight , \"","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"tweeted Dave Weigel of The Washington Post , over a pop-art cartoon of a woman","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"thinking ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"\" It should have been me... \"","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"\" When # Klomentum is more than a Twitter joke , \"","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"tweeted Edward Isaac-Dovere of the Atlantic .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"Klobuchar spokeswoman Carlie Waibel actually \" confirmed \" to The New York Times","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"that \" it ' s Klomentum , not Klobmentum . \"","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"One of the lessons of 2016 was that cheeseball clichés like \" the Big Mo , \" \" straight talk , \" and the \" beer test \" no longer had traction .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Voter calculations were about rage and nihilism :","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"They were done with catchphrases .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"Like amputees","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"who still feel","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"a leg is there ,","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"pundits continued speaking in this dead language ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"which widened the credibility gap further .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"Four years later , they ' re still doing it .","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"Kasich of all people was on CNN Tuesday night","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"talking about \" the Big Mo. \"","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"Van Jones wondered about the \" beer lane. \"","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"\" Klomentum \" is the relic","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"being flogged this morning .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"The \" firewall \" might be next .","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"The hapless Joe Biden , 2020 ' s clear answer to 2016 establishment Hindenburg Jeb Bush , finished a disastrous fifth in New Hampshire .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"Joe should drop out .","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"The world knows it .","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"The man shouldn ' t be driving ,","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"much less running for president .","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"Nonetheless ,","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"because Biden is perceived to have a \" firewall \" in the South","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"- the \" firewall \" of minority voters","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"enjoyed by this or that corporate-funded candidate is one of the more vile campaign clichés -","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"he will certainly not drop out .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"His campaign , even before Tuesday , was directing reporters to ignore New Hampshire","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"and look to Nevada , South Carolina , and Super Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"This means once again , it will likely be ( at least ) a five-person race through Super Tuesday , this time between Buttigieg , Klobuchar , Biden , Sanders , and Mike Bloomberg , the detestable oligarch","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"who has not even test-driven his eleventy-gazillion election-buying dollars yet .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"If Elizabeth Warren stays in","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"[ checks Twitter ] ,","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"the pie will be split in at least six big parts .","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"The Democratic Party ' s argument against Sanders for years has been his alleged inability","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"to grow beyond his base .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"Now , things have been arranged","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"so that he may not have to dispel these notions before Super Tuesday .","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"This may or may not be a good thing","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"- beating Trump is important","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"and the Democratic nominee should have to demonstrate the widest appeal -","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"but the brutal irony of Bernie Sanders","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"boosted by horse-race luck and conventional-wisdom miscalculation","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"is difficult to miss .","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"As with Republicans in 2016 , the defining characteristic of the 2020 Democratic race has been the unwieldy size of the field .","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"The same identity crisis","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"lurking under the Republican clown car","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"afflicted this year ' s Democratic contest :","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"Because neither donors nor party leaders nor pundits could figure out what they should be pretending to stand for ,","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"they couldn ' t coalesce around any one candidate .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"These constant mercurial shifts in \" momentum \"","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"- it ' s Pete !","depth":14},{"id":180,"text":"It ' s Amy !","depth":15},{"id":181,"text":"Paging Mike Bloomberg ! -","depth":15},{"id":182,"text":"have eroded the kingmaking power of the Democratic leadership .","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"They are eating the party from within ,","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"and seem poised to continue doing so .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"For Sanders supporters , the calculation has always been simpler :","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"Are you bought off , or not ?","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"Just by keeping to the right side of that one principle ,","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"Sanders will hold his 20-to-30 percent","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"and keep grinding toward victory ,","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"\" narrow \" wins or not .","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"It ' s a classic tortoise-and-hare story .","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"When you know where you ' re going ,","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"you tend to get there .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":387,"left":198,"right":386,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":0,"right":197,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":1,"right":196,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":196,"left":195,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":195,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":386,"left":272,"right":385,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":272,"left":264,"right":271,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":201,"right":263,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":5,"right":200,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":200,"left":6,"right":199,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":199,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":263,"left":220,"right":262,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":216,"right":219,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{